  {book: "Joel", book_num: 30, chapter_num: 2, verse_num: 2, content: "A day of darkness and gloominess, A day of clouds and deep  darkness, Like the dawn spread over the mountains - A people great and mighty. There has not been any like them Since eternity, And there will not be any more after them, Even until the years of the generation of the generations.", testament: "old", selected: nil},
  {book: "Joel", book_num: 30, chapter_num: 3, verse_num: 6, content: "And have sold to the children of the Javanim The children of Judah and the children of Jerusalem, In order to remove them Away from their borders;", testament: "old", selected: nil},
  {book: "Joel", book_num: 30, chapter_num: 3, verse_num: 18, content: "And in that day The mountains will drop down fresh wine, And the hills will flow with milk; And all the waterways of Judah Will flow with water, And a fountain will go forth from the house of Jehovah, And it will water the valley of Shittim.", testament: "old", selected: nil},
  {book: "Amos", book_num: 31, chapter_num: 2, verse_num: 4, content: "Thus says Jehovah, Because of three transgressions of Judah, Indeed, because of four, I will  not turn away the   punishment; Because they have rejected the law of Jehovah And have not kept His statutes; And their lies have caused them to  err, The lies which their fathers walked after.", testament: "old", selected: nil},
  {book: "Amos", book_num: 31, chapter_num: 4, verse_num: 7, content: "And I have also withheld the rain from you When there was yet three months until the harvest; And I made it rain on one city, But on another city I did not make it rain; One portion was rained on, And the portion that was not rained on dried up.", testament: "old", selected: nil},
  {book: "Amos", book_num: 31, chapter_num: 5, verse_num: 16, content: "Therefore thus says Jehovah, The God of hosts, the Lord: In all the open plazas there will be wailing, And in all the streets they will say, Alas! Alas! And they will call the farmer to mourning, And for wailing to those skilled in lamentation.", testament: "old", selected: nil},
  {book: "Amos", book_num: 31, chapter_num: 6, verse_num: 2, content: "Go over into Calneh, and see; And go from there to Hamath the great; Then go down to Gath of the Philistines. Are they better than these  kingdoms? Or is their territory greater than your territory?", testament: "old", selected: nil},
  {book: "Amos", book_num: 31, chapter_num: 6, verse_num: 10, content: "When his kinsman, that is, he who should burn his body, takes him up to bring his bones from the house, and says to him who is in the innermost part of the house, Are there any more with you, and that one says, None; then he will say, Hush, for the name of Jehovah should not be mentioned.", testament: "old", selected: nil},
  {book: "Amos", book_num: 31, chapter_num: 8, verse_num: 7, content: "Jehovah has sworn by the  excellency of Jacob, I shall by no means forget any of their deeds forever.", testament: "old", selected: nil},
