  {book: "Zephaniah", book_num: 36, chapter_num: 3, verse_num: 15, content: "Jehovah has taken away your judgments; He has turned aside your  enemy. The King of Israel, Jehovah, is in the midst of you; You will not  see evil again.", testament: "old", selected: nil},
  {book: "Zephaniah", book_num: 36, chapter_num: 3, verse_num: 17, content: "Jehovah your God in the midst of you Is a mighty One who saves; He will be jubilant over you with rejoicing; He will  rest in His love; He will exult over you with a ringing shout.", testament: "old", selected: nil},
  {book: "Haggai", book_num: 37, chapter_num: 2, verse_num: 13, content: "Then Haggai said, If one who is unclean because of a  corpse touches any of these, will it be unclean? And the priests answered and said, It will be unclean.", testament: "old", selected: nil},
  {book: "Haggai", book_num: 37, chapter_num: 2, verse_num: 14, content: "Then Haggai answered and said, So is this people and so is this nation before Me, declares Jehovah, and so is all the work of their hands. Thus what they offer there is unclean.", testament: "old", selected: nil},
  {book: "Zechariah", book_num: 38, chapter_num: 4, verse_num: 2, content: "And he said to me, What do you see? And I said, I see that there is a lampstand all of gold, with its bowl on top of it and its seven lamps upon it, with seven pipes for each of the lamps on top of it;", testament: "old", selected: nil},
  {book: "Zechariah", book_num: 38, chapter_num: 5, verse_num: 2, content: "And he said to me, What do you see? And I said, I see a flying scroll, its length twenty cubits and its breadth ten cubits.", testament: "old", selected: nil},
  {book: "Zechariah", book_num: 38, chapter_num: 6, verse_num: 13, content: "Indeed, it is He who will build the temple of Jehovah; and He will bear majesty and will sit and rule on His throne; and He will be a priest on His throne; and the counsel of peace will be between the two of them.", testament: "old", selected: nil},
  {book: "Zechariah", book_num: 38, chapter_num: 7, verse_num: 10, content: "And do not oppress the widow and the orphan, the stranger and the poor; and let none of you think evil in your hearts about his brother.", testament: "old", selected: nil},
  {book: "Zechariah", book_num: 38, chapter_num: 8, verse_num: 9, content: "Thus says Jehovah of hosts, Let your hands be strong, you who in these days hear these words from the mouth of the prophets who were there in the day when the foundation of the house of Jehovah of hosts, that is, the temple, was laid so that it might be built.", testament: "old", selected: nil},
  {book: "Zechariah", book_num: 38, chapter_num: 9, verse_num: 7, content: "And I will remove his blood from his mouth And his detestable things from  between his teeth; And he also will remain unto our  God; And he will be like a leader in  Judah, And Ekron will be like a Jebusite.", testament: "old", selected: nil},
  {book: "Zechariah", book_num: 38, chapter_num: 10, verse_num: 6, content: "And I will strengthen the house of  Judah, And I will save the house of  Joseph; And I will bring them back, for I  have had compassion on them; And they will be as though I had  not rejected them; For I am Jehovah their God, and I will answer them.", testament: "old", selected: nil},
  {book: "Zechariah", book_num: 38, chapter_num: 11, verse_num: 9, content: "Then I said, I will not shepherd you. What is to die will die, and what is to be destroyed will be destroyed, and those who are left will each eat one another's flesh.", testament: "old", selected: nil},
  {book: "Zechariah", book_num: 38, chapter_num: 12, verse_num: 10, content: "And I will pour out on the house of David and on the inhabitants of Jerusalem the Spirit of grace and of supplications; and they will look upon Me, whom they have pierced; and they will wail over Him with wailing as for an only son and cry bitterly over Him with bitter crying as for a firstborn son.", testament: "old", selected: nil},
  {book: "Zechariah", book_num: 38, chapter_num: 13, verse_num: 9, content: "And I will bring the third part  through fire And refine them as silver is  refined And try them as gold is tried. They will call on My name, And I will answer them; I will say, They are My people, And they will say, Jehovah is my  God.", testament: "old", selected: nil},
  {book: "Zechariah", book_num: 38, chapter_num: 14, verse_num: 2, content: "For I will gather all the nations against Jerusalem to battle; and the city will be captured, and the houses plundered, and the women ravished; and half of the city will go forth into captivity, but the rest of the people will not be cut off from the city.", testament: "old", selected: nil},
  {book: "Malachi", book_num: 39, chapter_num: 1, verse_num: 10, content: "Oh, that there were even someone among you who would shut the doors so that you would not kindle fire on My altar in vain! I have no delight in you, says Jehovah of hosts; and I am not pleased with the  sacrifice from your hand.", testament: "old", selected: nil},
  {book: "Malachi", book_num: 39, chapter_num: 3, verse_num: 5, content: "And I will draw near to you for judgment; and I will be a swift witness against the sorcerers and against the adulterers and against those who swear falsely and against those who oppress the hired worker for his hire, and the widow and the orphan, and those who turn the stranger aside, and who do not fear Me, says Jehovah of hosts.", testament: "old", selected: nil},
  {book: "Malachi", book_num: 39, chapter_num: 3, verse_num: 10, content: "Bring the whole tithe to the storehouse that there may be food in My house; and prove Me, if you will, by this, says Jehovah of hosts, whether I will open to you the windows of heaven and pour out blessing for you until there is no room for it.", testament: "old", selected: nil},
  {book: "Hosea", book_num: 29, chapter_num: 1, verse_num: 7, content: "But on the house of Judah I will have compassion and will save them by Jehovah their God, and I will not save them by bow or by sword or by battle, by horses or by horsemen.", testament: "old", selected: nil},
  {book: "Hosea", book_num: 29, chapter_num: 1, verse_num: 10, content: "But the number of the children of  Israel will be like the sand of the sea, Which cannot be measured or numbered; And in the place where it will be said to them, You are not My people, It will be said to them, You are  the sons of the living God.", testament: "old", selected: nil},
  {book: "Hosea", book_num: 29, chapter_num: 4, verse_num: 2, content: "Rather there are swearing and deceiving and murder And stealing and adultery; They are violent, And bloodshed follows bloodshed.", testament: "old", selected: nil},
  {book: "Hosea", book_num: 29, chapter_num: 4, verse_num: 6, content: "My people are destroyed Because of a lack of that  knowledge. For you have rejected that knowledge, And I will reject you, so that you will not be a priest to Me; Since you have forgotten the law of your God, I also will forget your children.", testament: "old", selected: nil},
  {book: "Hosea", book_num: 29, chapter_num: 6, verse_num: 4, content: "What shall I do with you,  O Ephraim? What shall I do with you,  O Judah? For your lovingkindness is like a morning cloud And like dew that departs early.", testament: "old", selected: nil},
  {book: "Hosea", book_num: 29, chapter_num: 7, verse_num: 16, content: "They return, but not to Him who is on high; They are like a deceitful bow. Their princes will fall by the sword Because of the rage of their tongue. This will be their derision In the land of Egypt.", testament: "old", selected: nil},
  {book: "Hosea", book_num: 29, chapter_num: 8, verse_num: 14, content: "For Israel has forgotten his Maker And has built  palaces, And Judah has multiplied fortified cities; But I will send fire into his cities, And it will devour its palaces.", testament: "old", selected: nil},
  {book: "Hosea", book_num: 29, chapter_num: 9, verse_num: 4, content: "They will not pour out offerings of wine to Jehovah, Neither will their sacrifices be pleasing to Him; They will be to them as the bread of mourning; All who eat them will be  unclean, For their bread will be for  themselves; It will not come into the house of Jehovah.", testament: "old", selected: nil},
  {book: "Hosea", book_num: 29, chapter_num: 11, verse_num: 2, content: "As they called them, So they went from them; To the Baals they sacrificed, And to the idols they burned incense.", testament: "old", selected: nil},
